<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-01T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.20/57: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General in Martinique (<persName type="from">Malige</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort-de-France</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-01T17:00:00-04:00">June 1,
                                    1942—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>203. Department’s No. 115, May 31. From Reber. In conversation with
                            Robert today I explained the Department’s position as set forth in
                            telegram under reference. He appreciates necessity for early conclusion
                            of negotiations and since arrival of preliminary instructions embodied
                            in his “provisional reply” has continued to press <pb facs="0645" n="639" xml:id="pg_639"/> Vichy for a definite answer as well as
                            authority for early departure <hi rend="italic">Sagittaire</hi>. He has
                            been informed answer will be sent as soon as Laval returns to Vichy
                            tomorrow.</p>
                        <p>I have sent Atherton by airmail this morning a copy of Robert’s memo<note n="1" xml:id="d631fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_640">p.
                                640</ref>.</note> together with comments. Admiral Hoover has also
                            been furnished copies. [Reber.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Malige</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>